---

{% from "components/hidden-input/macro.njk" import hiddenInput %}
{% from "components/form/macro.njk" import form %}
{% from "components/label/macro.njk" import label %}
{% from "components/text-input/macro.njk" import textInput %}
{% from "components/button/macro.njk" import button %}
{% from "components/field/macro.njk" import field %}

<h2>Session round-trip</h2>
<p>Hidden inputs carry server-side state across a form submission
  without exposing it to the user. Typical uses: CSRF tokens,
  pagination cursors, selected-item ids.</p>

{% call form({ action: "/apply/step/2", label: "Application step" }) %}
  {{ hiddenInput({ name: "csrf_token", value: "demo-csrf-abc123" }) }}
  {{ hiddenInput({ name: "application_id", value: "A-2026-0042" }) }}

  {% call field() %}
    {{ label({ for: "phone", text: "Phone number" }) }}
    {{ textInput({ id: "phone", name: "phone", inputmode: "tel" }) }}
  {% endcall %}

  {{ button({ text: "Continue", type: "submit" }) }}
{% endcall %}

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<p>Hidden inputs are not exposed to assistive tech at all. Do not
  put content in <code>params.value</code> that a user would need to
  read — this is for server-round-trip data only.</p>
